context: The San Diego Symphony at Symphony Towers performs on a regular basis and is directed by <a0_0><b5_0>Jahja Ling<b5_0/><a0_0/>. The San Diego Opera at Civic Center Plaza, directed by Ian Campbell, was ranked by Opera America as <a4_0><b9_0>one of the top 10 opera companies in the United States<b9_0/><a4_0/>. Old Globe Theatre at Balboa Park produces about 15 plays and musicals annually. The <a1_0><b6_0>La Jolla Playhouse at UCSD<b6_0/><a1_0/> is directed by Christopher Ashley. Both the Old Globe Theatre and the La Jolla Playhouse have produced the world premieres of plays and musicals that have gone on to win Tony Awards or nominations on Broadway. The Joan B. Kroc Theatre at Kroc Center's Performing Arts Center is a 600-seat state-of-the-art theatre that hosts music, dance, and theatre performances. The <a2_0><b7_0>San Diego Repertory Theatre at the Lyceum Theatres<b7_0/><a2_0/> in Horton Plaza produces a variety of plays and musicals. Hundreds of movies and a dozen TV shows have been filmed in San Diego, a tradition going back as far as <a3_0><b8_0>1898<b8_0/><a3_0/>.
